==English==
===Alternative spellings===
*[[nartjie]]
===Etymology===
From Tamil ''nartei'' through Afrikaans. Has been used in South Africa since 1790, but the first written recorded English use is by Graham Green in the ''Tavern of the Seas'' 1947.
===Noun===

'''naartjie'''

# (South African) Citrus reticulata: Citris nobilis: ([[Mandarin]], [[Satsuma]] and [[Tangerine]]). A soft loose-skinned tangerine.

